Wash and dry produce. Dice @tomato{1%unit} into 1/2-inch pieces.

Melt half the @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} (large pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add diced tomato, @tomato paste{1%unit}, and @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @Vidalia onion paste{1/2%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{3%unit}, and 3 cups water (6 cups for 4). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer.

Meanwhile, remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}.

Once soup is simmering, add @tortelloni{9%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, ~{2%minutes}.

Add kale; stir to combine. Return soup to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until tortelloni are tender and kale has wilted, ~{1-3%minutes}.
> TIP: Increase heat if necessary to maintain a simmer.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Meanwhile, halve and toast @ciabatta bread{1%unit}. Spread cut sides of bread with remaining garlic herb butter; halve on a diagonal.

Divide soup between bowls; top each bowl with a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Serve with garlic bread on the side.